PatientClinicTextClinic Letter Text-enumeratedDirectorystringOptional-You recently attended the Fracture Liaison Serviceintrostartfor your broken bone.introendAs part of your routine NHS care you should have tests to make sure your bones are strong because 15% of patients will break another bone in the next 2 years. introaddinfoWe would like to invite you to attend an appointment with the Fracture Prevention Nurses. This is to find out if you need further specialized treatment to protect you from breaking any more bones. aptinviteWe have enclosed the appointment details for you. If this is not convenient then please give us a call so that we can rebook you for a more convenient time. We have also enclosed a blood test card for you to have done at your GP survery at least 2 weeks before your appointment. appointmentinfoIf you have any further questions please do not hesitate to contact us at the number at the top right of this page and we will be pleased to help you. outroAm I at risk of osteoporosis leafletEnclosure1Appointment Letter and Blood Card for Patient. Enclosure2PRIVATE AND CONFIDENTIALPrivateAndConfidentialLabelWe would like to invite you to attend a Bone Marrow Density Scan. This is a quick and painless test. This is a specialist OPEN Scanner (you can just lay on the couch) and the radiographer will be with you all the time. DXAInviteIf the scan suggests your bones are thinner than we would expect we will then invite you to an appointment at a later date to discuss the results of your scan. Any additional appointments will be sent out separately to this letter. DXAInfo

PatientMonitoringLetterTextMonitoring Letter Text-enumeratedDirectorystringOptional-As part of your treatment for osteoporosis, you kindly returned the questionnaire about the health of your bones. We like to follow up with everyone to check that you are managing with the medication you have been recommendedMonIntroStartmedication that you have been recommended.MonIntroEndYou are taking the medication and are not experiencing any other problems with your treatment plan. ComplianceWe are pleased to see you have had your injection and assume you are not experiencing any other problems with your treatment plan. Please continue every 6 months. Your GP will need to arrange a blood test prior to each injection. Please ensure you register with the Prolong programme to receive reminders (the registration form was with your original letter from us or you can email prolong.support@nhs.net or call 01223 436441) The injections should not be stopped without consultation with the metabolic bone service.DemabThank you for taking the time to help us ensure you are receiving the best possible osteoporosis treatment. We will contact you again in about 9 months to see how you are getting on. If you have any other questions or queries, please do not hesitate to contact us on the number above or our email address.OutroThank you for taking the time to help us ensure you are receiving the best possible osteoporosis treatment.
